<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1185,1434,1685]" pageId="8" pageNumber="801">
<emphasis box="[138,252,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="801">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Colonies with unbranched stems. Main cauline tube with single hydrothecate internodes with two to five infrathecal nematothecae and occasionally with extra suprathecal nematotheca. Without node between cauline apophyses and hydrocladia; occasionally, however, present and then cauline apophyses with two or three nematothecae. Hydrocladia up to 12th order. Hydrocladia divided into hydrothecate internodes. Unforked hydrocladial internode with one or two infrathecal nematothecae at approximately same level. Hydrotheca deep. Forked hydrocladial internodes with one to three infrathecal nematothecae; hydrocladial apophyses with two or three nematothecae.
</paragraph>
